%description:
Deterministic end-to-end MLDv1 exchange test (RFC 2710).

Mirrors the six observable checks from IGMP_basic.test, translated to IPv6/MLD
via Mldv1 EV_INFO markers (Mldv1 has no TestMLD subclass, outputFile, or
IScriptable interface; state-string dumps are not available).
Membership is driven by real apps (UdpSink with multicastGroup), the production path.

IGMP_basic check mapping:

Check 1 (host joined ff02::1 on startup):
  Implicit -- ff02::1 (ALL_NODES_2) is joined automatically by every IPv6 node.
  Not directly assertable via EV_INFO without an outputFile mechanism. Verified
  implicitly: if the host receives the router's General Query (directed to ff02::1),
  the node must have ff02::1 registered.

Check 2 (router joined ff02::2 on startup):
  Implicit -- ff02::2 (ALL_ROUTERS_2) is joined automatically by IPv6 routers.
  Not directly assertable. Verified implicitly: Done messages are sent to ff02::2
  by the host after leaving (MLD §8.2), and the router processes them.

Check 3 (host joins ff0e::1 -> Report sent immediately):
  host runs UdpSink with multicastGroup="ff0e::1".  Socket join at t=0 fires
  ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> Mldv1::multicastGroupJoined -> unsolicited
  Multicast Listener Report sent.
  ASSERTED: "sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1 on iface="

Check 4 (router receives Report, records listener):
  The router receives host's Report and records the listener (No Listeners
  Present --> Listeners Present). TWO markers are asserted:
  - "received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1"
  - "recorded listener for group=ff0e::1"

Check 5 (host leaves ff0e::1 -> Done sent immediately):
  host's UdpSink has stopTime=5s. Socket close fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal
  -> Mldv1::multicastGroupLeft -> Done sent to ff02::2 (ALL_ROUTERS_2).
  ASSERTED: "sending Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1 on iface="

Check 6 (router removes listener after lastListenerQueryCount * lastListenerQueryInterval):
  On receiving the Done, the router sends a Multicast-Address-Specific Query
  (Listeners Present --> Checking Listeners). With no Reply, the leave timer
  fires and the group is removed (EV_DEBUG only -- processLeaveTimer emits only
  EV_DEBUG). Asserted indirectly:
  - MAS Query sent: "sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::1"
  - No further "recorded listener for group=ff0e::1" after the Done confirms
    the group was not re-registered; the MAS-Query proof suffices.
  - Router receives the Done: "received Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1"

Additionally asserted (bonus): the router's initial General Query is received by
the host (confirms the querier path is active and the host is in the ff02::1 group).

Network: host (StandardHost6) and router (Router6) connect via a shared EthernetHub.
Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns addresses. hasMld=true on both nodes.
dupAddrDetectTransmits=0 eliminates DAD delay. seed-set=0 pins RNG.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network MldBasicNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = MldBasicNetwork
sim-time-limit = 20s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# Fix RNG seed for deterministic behavior of uniform(0, maxRespTime) in startHostTimer
seed-set = 0

eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# Enable MLD on all nodes so the host can receive Queries and the router can receive Reports/Dones
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
# Disable DAD for fast startup (no 1s+ delay before addresses become ready)
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# Check 4/6: activate the real querier on the router.
# Must be set at the node (Router6) level: NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates
#   *.multicastForwarding = this.multicastForwarding
# to all submodules (including ipv6.routingTable), overriding any per-submodule setting.
**.router.multicastForwarding = true

# Router timing: short startupQueryInterval so the General Query fires before the host leaves;
# long queryInterval so periodic Queries do not interfere with the end-to-end chain.
**.router.ipv6.mld.startupQueryInterval = 2s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryInterval = 100s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryResponseInterval = 1s
# lastListenerQueryInterval=1s, lastListenerQueryCount=2: leave timer = 2s (well within 20s).
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastListenerQueryInterval = 1s
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastListenerQueryCount = 2
# multicastListenerInterval=6s: ensures the listener entry stays alive until the Done arrives at t=5s.
**.router.ipv6.mld.multicastListenerInterval = 6s

# Check 3: host joins ff0e::1 via UdpSink (fires ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> unsolicited Report).
**.host.numApps = 1
**.host.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1"
# Check 5: host leaves ff0e::1 at t=5s via socket close (fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal -> Done).
# After the General Query at t=2s, host's flag=true -> Done is sent for ff0e::1 at t=5s.
**.host.app[0].stopTime = 5s

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Check 3: host sends unsolicited Multicast Listener Report for ff0e::1 on join
%# Proves: group registered on host immediately; Non-Listener --> Delaying Listener (Report sent)
%contains: stdout
MldBasicNetwork.host.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1 on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Check 4a: router receives the Report for ff0e::1 from the host
%# Proves: router is active as querier and sees the Report on the shared segment
%contains: stdout
MldBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1 iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Check 4b: router records the listener for ff0e::1 (No Listeners Present --> Listeners Present)
%# "recorded listener" is only emitted on the FIRST recording
%contains: stdout
MldBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: recorded listener for group=ff0e::1

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Bonus: host receives the router's General Query at t=2s (proves ff02::1 membership is active)
%contains: stdout
MldBasicNetwork.host.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received General Listener Query on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Check 5: host sends Multicast Listener Done for ff0e::1 at t=5s (socket close)
%# Proves: group removed from host immediately; host sends Done because flag=true after Query-driven Report
%contains: stdout
MldBasicNetwork.host.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1 on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Check 6a: router receives the Done for ff0e::1 from the host
%# Proves: Done message propagated from host to router on the shared segment
%contains: stdout
MldBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1 iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Check 6b: router sends Multicast-Address-Specific Query after receiving the Done
%# Proves: Listeners Present --> Checking Listeners transition (MAS Query triggers last-listener countdown)
%contains: stdout
MldBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::1 on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Undisposed-object guard: verify no leaked cMessage or cObject at end of run
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
